\section{Glossary}
MIF - minor frame; a smallest unit of L1 data  \\
MAF - major frame; MAF contains 135 MIFs; ; there are 3500 MAFs in a day \\
\ \\
RC info - tells how a row or a column is laid out (this is only information, not data)
 

